title.narrative: OUTPUT 5.2.1: EVIDENCE BASED SOCIAL PROTECTION POLICIES

description.narrative: By 2025, national actors have strengthened capacities to develop and implement evidence-based, gender-sensitive public policies on social protection that contribute to improving the resilience of the most disadvantaged, so that the national system expands its coverage and intervention packages to reach more children., which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Evaluation, Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Reducing Child Poverty, Reducing Child Poverty (Covid), Research. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2025 girls, boys, and youth in disadvantaged areas (urban, rural, and peri-urban) have increased equitable access to social protection and other basic social services for enhanced resilience to different socio-economic shocks.

description.narrative: In 2021 the CO contributed to strengthening the social protection sector through: (i) measuring monetary child poverty; (ii) developing a concept note and a roadmap for the elaboration of a new national social protection policy; (iii) strengthening the monitoring mechanisms of the social protection policy through support for sectoral implementation reviews of the earlier (2018-2020) policy and of progress toward universal health coverage (UHC) at the decentralized level. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:27/01/2022
